step.context:
\text{If }\ora{AB}=\vector{2}{-4}{5}\text{ and }
\ora{AC}=\vector{1}{-2}{-3}. \\
\text{represent the adjacent sides of a parallelogram} \\
\text{does the following represent its diagonal AD?}

step.reason:
\text{For any vector }\ora{A}\text{ its unit vector }
\hat A=\dfrac{\ora{A}}{\ora{|A|}} \\
\therefore \hat{AD}
  =\dfrac{\vector{3}{-6}{2}}{\sqrt{3^2+(-6)^2+2^2}}
  =\dfrac{1}{7}(\vector{3}{-6}{2})

